%% Auction System Data Flow - Bid Placement
%% Format: Mermaid Sequence Diagram
%% Last Updated: 2024-01-15

sequenceDiagram
    participant C as Client
    participant GW as API Gateway
    participant RL as Rate Limiter (Redis)
    participant BS as Bid Service
    participant DL as Distributed Lock (Redis)
    participant PS as Payment Service
    participant DB as PostgreSQL
    participant OB as Outbox Publisher
    participant K as Kafka
    participant NS as Notification Service

    C->>GW: POST /api/v1/bids<br/>(JWT + Correlation-ID)
    
    Note over GW: Correlation ID middleware<br/>Generate/Forward UUID v4
    
    GW->>RL: Check rate limit
    RL-->>GW: Allowed (sliding window)
    
    Note over GW: Auth + RBAC validation<br/>Circuit breaker wraps call
    
    GW->>BS: Forward request<br/>(mTLS + service token)
    
    Note over BS: Input validation<br/>(pkg/validation)
    
    BS->>DL: Acquire lock<br/>(auction:{id}, fencing token)
    DL-->>BS: Lock acquired (token: N)
    
    BS->>PS: Hold funds (service token)
    
    Note over PS: SELECT FOR UPDATE<br/>on wallet row
    
    PS->>DB: BEGIN + Hold + Outbox entry
    DB-->>PS: COMMIT
    PS-->>BS: Hold confirmed

    BS->>DB: BEGIN + Place bid
    DB-->>BS: COMMIT
    
    BS->>DL: Release lock (verify token N)
    DL-->>BS: Released
    
    BS-->>GW: 201 Created
    GW-->>C: 201 Created

    Note over OB: Background polling (1s interval)
    OB->>DB: SELECT unpublished outbox entries
    OB->>K: Publish events (event_id: UUID v4)
    OB->>DB: UPDATE published_at

    K->>NS: Consume bid.placed event
    
    Note over NS: Idempotency check<br/>(Redis processed-events store)
    
    NS->>C: WebSocket notification
